verses.roman:
bālya-kāla haite tomāra ye kailuṅ sevana
tāra ei phala more deha nārāyaṇa

synonyms: bālya-kāla haite—from my childhood; tomāra—Your; ye—whatever; kailuṅ—I have done; sevana—service; tāra—of that; ei phala—this result; more—unto me; deha—kindly award; nārāyaṇa—O Supreme Lord.
translation: "My dear Lord, kindly bestow this benediction as a result of whatever service I have rendered unto You from my childhood.
